# Store and check out every text file with LF on all platforms, so a checkout is
# byte-for-byte identical no matter the contributor's OS. `text=auto` still lets
# git detect binary files and leave them untouched. Uniform line endings are what
# let content-exact checks pass everywhere: `eph skills check` compares the tracked
# skill copies under .claude/ and .agents/ against the LF source embedded in the
# binary, and cargo fmt expects LF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# LF pins for files where CRLF is not cosmetic but a bug: POSIX shell scripts and
# the git pre-commit hook fail to run on Unix with CRLF line endings. Keep them LF
# even if the blanket rule above is ever relaxed to native checkout.
*.sh        text eol=lf
.githooks/* text eol=lf
